Grizzlies Defeat Thunder 101-93 in OT, Take Lead in NBA Playoff Series

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-08T00:11:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/grizzlies-defeat-thunder-101-93-in-ot-take-lead-in-nba-playoff-series.html
The  Memphis  Grizzlies defeated the
Oklahoma City Thunder 101-93 in overtime to take a 2-1 lead in
their National Basketball Association playoff series.  Zach Randolph had 21 points and Mike Conley and O.J. Mayo
each added 18 for the Grizzlies at FedEx Forum in Memphis.  Russell Westbrook scored 23 and  Kevin Durant  had 22 for the
Thunder.  Game 4 in the best-of-seven series will be held May 9 in
Memphis.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  